    "reading": "The eight B3 defect-mask column profiles are not atlas labels: each is determined by intrinsic bilinear data of the (signature, square) pair -- the affine defect, the zero pattern of the error matrix B (uniform x*J vs a zero side), and the error space D = span(B).  Both the zero pattern and D are needed (dropping either creates exactly one collision), and together with the signature they determine the profile with zero collisions over all 60 records.  In particular the {DM01,DM02} split that item 5 attributed to a mask-transport support residue is exactly the B zero-pattern dichotomy, and the support Sigma is a consequence of the factorization of B, not an independent input.",
