    "statement": "For every B3 endpoint-24 record, the defect-mask column profile is a function of the intrinsic pair (selected signature S, bilinear error matrix B of the source square): the affine defect delta = |supp E|, the zero pattern of B (uniform vs one zero side), and the error space D = span(B).  Over all 60 records this key has zero collisions and recovers all eight profiles; dropping either the zero pattern or D introduces exactly one collision, so both intrinsic coordinates are necessary.  No mask-transport support residue is required."
